        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/bervo/BERVO_9000004"/>
        <obo:IAO_0000115>The rate at which phosphate ions move through aqueous media due to concentration gradients and ionic mobility. This parameter controls phosphate transport in soil water and surface waters and is critical for modeling phosphorus cycling and nutrient transport in terrestrial and aquatic ecosystems.</obo:IAO_0000115>
